# UI/UX Pro Max

Comprehensive design guide for web and mobile applications. Contains 67 styles, 96 color palettes, 57 font pairings, 99 UX guidelines, and 25 chart types across 13 technology stacks. Searchable database with priority-based recommendations.

## Quick Reference

### 1. Accessibility (CRITICAL)
- `color-contrast` - Minimum 4.5:1 ratio for normal text
- `focus-states` - Visible focus rings on interactive elements
- `aria-labels` - aria-label for icon-only buttons

### 2. Touch & Interaction (CRITICAL)
- `touch-target-size` - Minimum 44x44px touch targets
- `cursor-pointer` - Add cursor-pointer to clickable elements

### 3. Performance (HIGH)
- `image-optimization` - Use WebP, srcset, lazy loading
- `reduced-motion` - Check prefers-reduced-motion

### 4. Layout & Responsive (HIGH)
- `readable-font-size` - Minimum 16px body text on mobile
- `z-index-management` - Define z-index scale (10, 20, 30, 50)

### 5. Typography & Color (MEDIUM)
- `line-height` - Use 1.5-1.75 for body text
- `line-length` - Limit to 65-75 characters per line

## How to Use This Skill

When working on UI/UX tasks (design, implementation, or review), follow this workflow:

### Step 1: Generate Design System
**Always start by generating a design system** to get tailored recommendations:

```bash
python3 ui-ux-pro-max-skill/src/ui-ux-pro-max/scripts/search.py "<product_type> <industry> <keywords>" --design-system -p "Vue Pure Admin Max"
```

### Step 2: Persist Design System
To save the design system for future reference in this project:

```bash
python3 ui-ux-pro-max-skill/src/ui-ux-pro-max/scripts/search.py "<query>" --design-system --persist -p "Vue Pure Admin Max"
```
This creates `design-system/MASTER.md` as the source of truth.

### Step 3: Domain-Specific Search
Use detailed searches for specific components or styles:

```bash
python3 ui-ux-pro-max-skill/src/ui-ux-pro-max/scripts/search.py "<query>" --domain <domain> --stack vue
```

**Available Domains:**
- `style`: UI styles (glassmorphism, minimalism, etc.)
- `color`: Color palettes
- `typography`: Font pairings
- `landing`: Page structure and CTA strategies
- `chart`: Chart type recommendations
- `ux`: Best practices and anti-patterns
- `product`: Product type specific UI recommendations

**Available Stacks:** `vue`, `html-tailwind`, `react`, `nextjs`, etc. (Use `vue` for this project)
